summary: Skyrim INIs HQ Settings AIO without huge performance loss!
descriptionHtml:
[b][size=2][font=Verdana][color=#ffff00]
[color=#ffffff]WOW ... 350 endorsements I'm glad to see now ... many many many thanks to you!!![/color]
[color=#ffffff]
Every feedback to my tweaked INIs are welcome to make them better in future!!!

New screenshot(s) and update(s) will be coming soon as possible, if I have the time for it!!!
[/color][color=#00ff00]
[/color][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]======[/color][/color][/color]
[color=#ff0000][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]NEW(S):[/color]
[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]======[/color][/color][/color][/color][/color]


[font=Verdana][color=#ffff00]Latest Version:
[/color][/font][color=#00ff00][color=#ffff00]
[color=#00ff00]TESV INIs HQ Settings Private Pure Version 1.0.17
[/color][/color]
[color=#ffff00]In my opinion with the best of harmless tweaks I have ever made more optimized with a really good balance between look and performance in a (hard) modded game I am self using now!!![/color][/color][color=#ffff00]
[b][size=2][font=Verdana][b][size=2][font=Verdana]
Important: I have changed all to the manual download option only, which make sense on this release!!! [/font][/size][/b][/font][/size][/b][/color]


[/font][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]=================[/color][/color][/color]
Global Information:
[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]=================[/color][/color][/color]

[size=2][font=Verdana]Hi there,
[b][size=2][size=2][font=Verdana]
a guide of my mod installation does not exist at the moment here. I cannot see the release date for a new guide till now or in future, because I am very busy - my main problem, which is caused by my job.
I have a lot of modded content changed/optimized or cut, which needs/have needed time enough. If you are interested in the content of my actually modded game, I can share informations about it via pm to you!!!
Older version(s) I have not released here anymore cannot be supported -I am so sorry!!! For this reason I have added the old website content with descriptions of these under "Miscellaneous files"[size=2][font=Verdana], if you are interested in[/font][/size]!!![/font][/size][/size][/b]

Cheers,

Astra2000  [/font][color=#ff0000][color=#ffff00]

[/color][/color][/size]
[b][size=2]=======================
Some general informations:
=======================
[/size][/b]
My first player character SALINA you can find a pic under my screenshots section is available as a follower mod by Skykix you can find [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/86903/?]here[/url] on NEXUS!!!

[b][size=2]For mod installations I actually use the latest [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/6194]MO[/url] under the section "Miscellaneous files" for the Oldrim!!![/size][/b]

The ENB-Preset I use is the latest final (not the actually beta) [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/41482/?]Rudy ENB NLA[/url] by Rudy102!!!

========================
Some words about ENB stuff:
========================

What can I say ... mmh ... I have tested many of ENB-Presets and it is not easy to find the right good one to be able to use mainly for gaming only!?! But it is most dependent of used mods and how many you will have installed in your game on the end!!!

[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]=====================[/color][/color][/color]
Additional Informations:
[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]=====================[/color][/color][/color]

[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]HQ = High Quality:

All my created tweaked INIs are based on default with "Ultra Settings" to run proper or best with using ENB-Presets!!!

[b][size=2][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]=====================[/color][/color][/color][b][size=2][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff][b][size=2][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]====[/color][/color][/color][/size][/b][/color][/color][/color][/size][/b]
More Additional Informations:
[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]=====================[/color][/color][/color][/size][/b][b][size=2][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff][b][size=2][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]====[/color][/color][/color][/size][/b][/color][/color][/color][/size][/b]

I[/color][/color][/color][b][size=2]f you have problems with 2K and higher Textures or Blood Mods then try this[/size][/b] using MO:

Open SkyrimPrefs.ini, search the following section and delete them!!!

[Display]
iTexMipMapMinimum=0
iTexMipMapSkip=0  

More about it here:

[color=#ffff00][url=http://forum.step-project.com/topic/6697-textures-not-appearing-in-game-using-mod-organizer/]http://forum.step-project.com/topic/6697-textures-not-appearing-in-game-using-mod-organizer/[/url]
[/color]
[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]===============[/color][/color][/color]
[color=#ffffff]Additional Notes:
[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]===============[/color][/color][/color][/color]

IMPORTANT:
Please use only my release, if you have a powerful graphic card, CPU 4 Cores or higher and 4GB or more RAM!!!


INSTALLATION:

1. Please make a backup from your own before and change both of my released INIs to your language, to your graphic card and monitor resolution in the SkyrimPrefs.ini!!!

2. Unpack and replace with your INIs you can find in ... Documents\My Games\Skyrim and for ModOrganizer\profiles\the profile you want to use in your game!!!

[color=#ffff00][color=#ff00ff][color=#ffffff]3. That's all - have fun!!![/color][/color][/color]

[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]===============================[/color][/color][/color][/color][/color]
[color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ff00ff][color=#ffffff][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ff00ff][color=#ffffff]Some help for beginners (by Imrazon):
[/color][/color][/color][/color][/color][/color][/color][/color][/color][/color][/color][/color][/color][color=#ffff00][color=#ffff00][color=#ffffff]===============================[/color][/color][/color]

To adapt my Inis to your system and game:
Open my skyrimprefs.ini with an editor, preferably with  [url=http://notepad-plus-plus.org/download/]Notepad++[/url]  search the line sD3DDevice= and type in your graphic card behind = . If you do not know, what to write in here, open your back uped skyrimprefs.ini. There you find under the same line the correct identification of your graphic card. Just copy all what is behind = and paste it also behind = in my skyrimprefs.ini. Don´t forget the quotation marks!
 
If you use a different ENB preset you may also adapt the line fGamma=1.4000. Other ENB presets require a differnet value here. I.G. RealVison ENB by SkyrimTuner requires the value 1.2400, Rudy ENB requires the value 1.0000. To get the correct value I recommend to read the description of the ENB
preset you use. In case you can´t find any Information about that don´t shy to ask the publisher of this ENB preset in the comments.
 
My Inis are setted for use with mouse and keyboard. If you use a game pad, I recommend to open the menu after starting the game and change the settings there. That´s the easiest way. I recommend to deactivate gamepad rumble.

A global Note to all my INIs:
I can't garant that the settings runs on every machine. That's your choice to test it or leave it, please!!![u]

[/u]About this page:
This side will be updated very often to get better structure when I have the time for it!!!  :=)[u][u][u]
[/u][/u][/u]
